column8: I have read, or have had read to me in my native language, and I understand the Participant Information Sheet.
column9: I have been given sufficient time to consider whether or not to participate in this research/study/clinical trial.
column10: I have had the opportunity to use a translator, legal representative, family support or a friend to help me ask questions and understand the proposed research/study/clinical trial.
column11: I am satisfied with the answers that have been given regarding the research/study/clinical trial and I have a copy of this consent form and information sheet.
column12: I understand that taking part in this study is voluntary (my choice).
column13: I give consent to the research staff for collecting and processing of my information, including those about my general health.
column14: I am assured that confidentiality of the data will be maintained.
column15: I understand that I will be given a copy of my results.
column16: I understand that I neither have to bear any expenses nor receive any financial aid for participating.
column17: I understand that I may withdraw from the study at any time.
column18: If I decide to withdraw from participating, I agree that the information or data collected about me up to the time of withdrawal may be utilized.
column19: I know who to contact if I have any questions about the study in general.
column20: I understand my responsibilities as a participant.
